The '''canine''', usually short for '''dog or other canine''', is a [[monster class]] that appears in ''[[NetHack]]'', and is represented by the lowercase [[d]] glyph ({{white|d}}). Dogs and canines are designated internally by the macro <code>'''S_DOG'''</code>.{{refsrc|include/monsym.h|18|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}

The class contains the following monsters:{{refsrc|src/monst.c|196|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}

* {{monsymlink|jackal}}
* {{monsymlink|fox}}
* {{monsymlink|coyote}}
* {{monsymlink|werejackal (animal)}}
* {{monsymlink|little dog}}
* {{monsymlink|dingo}}
* {{monsymlink|dog}}
* {{monsymlink|large dog}}
* {{monsymlink|wolf}}
* {{monsymlink|werewolf (animal)}}
* {{monsymlink|winter wolf cub}}
* {{monsymlink|warg}}
* {{monsymlink|winter wolf}}
* {{monsymlink|hell hound pup}}
* {{monsymlink|hell hound}}
* [[Deferred]] monsters
** {{monsymlink|Cerberus}}

==Common traits==
Canines are quadrupedal and [[carnivorous]] [[animal]]s; they lack [[hands]], and are visible via [[infravision]]. Canines can be separated into four broad categories: 

* [[Domestic]] dogs: the little dog, dog and large dog
* [[Werecreature]]s: the animal forms of the werewolf and werejackal
* 'Ordinary' canines: jackals, foxes, coyotes, dingoes, and wolves
* Fantastic canines: wargs, winter wolves and their cubs, hell hounds and their pups, and Cerberus

Canines primarily attack via bites, and the fantastic canines except for the warg also have a [[breath]] weapon.

Canines are either of [[neutral]] [[alignment]] as with the warg and mundane canine monsters, or they are [[chaotic]] as with the canine [[werecreature]]s and the other fantastic canines. [[Chatting]] to a tame canine monster can be used [[#Messages|to gauge its current condition]].

Canines that eat [[mimic]] corpses may assume the form of a [[sink]] or [[tripe ration]] for the duration of the meal if they do not assume a monster-specific form.{{refsrc|src/dogmove.c|1352|nethack=3.6.7}}{{refsrc|src/dogmove.c|1354|nethack=3.6.7}} Monsters that [[polymorph]] into any canine monster - excluding werecreatures assuming their animal form - will produce a specific message if this occurs out of the [[hero]]'s sight.{{refsrc|src/mon.c|4225|nethack=3.6.7|name="smell"}}

===Generation===
Randomly generated canines that are not domestic are always created hostile; domestic canines are sometimes peaceful towards neutral characters.

The canine is the first [[quest]] [[monster class]] for [[Samurai]], and makes up {{frac|24|175}} of the monsters randomly generated on the [[Samurai quest]]. Some random canines are also generated on a few levels within the quest branch at level creation: one each is placed randomly on every floor between the home and goal levels, and two are randomly placed on the goal level itself.

